Pre-heat your oven to 180 degrees and bring a large #pot{} of water to the boil with a
pinch of @salt{}. Peel and finely chop the @garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop the
@flat leaf parsley{2}(finely chopped) and @mint{1}(finely chopped) and grate the
zest of the @lemon{1}. Chop the @potato{2} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Mix together your garlic, parsley, mint, lemon zest and @dukkah mix{6} in a #bowl{},
along with a splash of @olive oil{}, a pinch of salt and a good grind of
@black pepper{}.

Drizzle some oil onto a #baking tray{}, place each @pork medallion{4} on the tray
and press your herby dukkah mix onto the top of your pork. Put in your oven to
cook for ~{15%minutes}.

> The pork is fully cooked when there is no pink remaining.

Pop your potato into the pot of boiling water and cook for ~{12-15%minutes}.

> The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

Once your potato is cooked, drain, pop back in the pot and add a knob of
@?butter{1%knob}. Crush lightly with a #fork{} and season with a pinch of salt and
a grind of pepper.

Add some oil, the juice from your lemon, a pinch of salt and a good grind of
pepper to your @lambs lettuce and bulls blood leaves{2}(washed) mix.

Slice and serve your pork with your potato and salad on the side. Enjoy!